<A href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=inetd&amp;
sektion=8&amp;manpath=OpenBSD+3.7">inetd(8)</A> 
e <A href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=nc&amp;
sektion=1&amp;manpath=OpenBSD+3.7">nc(1)</A>. 
La seguente riga di <TT>/etc/inetd.conf</TT> crea un socket in ascolto 
limitato all'indirizzo di loopback (127.0.0.1) e alla porta 5000. 
d320 6
d327 1
a327 6
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<TT>127.0.0.1:5000 stream tcp nowait nobody /usr/bin/nc nc -w 
  \<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;20 192.168.1.10 80 </TT>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

